The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, July 16, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Friday, July 16, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Prince Anwar Shah Road and SP Mukherjee Road. Dug up to lay water pipes.				 																Career fair				 																																	Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will inaugurate Career Plan 2004, a mega career fair, organised in association with West Bengal State Council of Technical Education, at Netaji Indoor Stadium, 3 pm.				 																Theatre				 																																	A play-reading programme will be presented by members of amateur theatre group Spotlight at American Center, 7 pm. By invitation only.				 																Reading				 																																	Amitav Ghosh will read from his latest book The Hungry Tide at Oxford Bookstore, 6.30 pm. Novelist Sunil Gangopadhyay and environmentalist Tushar Kanjilal will attend.				 																Music				 																																	A seminar on appreciation of Hindustani classical music, conducted by Pt Buddhadeb Dasgupta, at Bharatiyam, Salt Lake, 6.30 pm.				 																Budget talk				 																																	A panel discussion on Will the Union Budget 2004-05 stimulate growth and investment?, organised by Bharat Chamber of Commerce, at The Park, 11.30 am.				 																Art beat				 																																	Summer Show, an all-India exhibition of paintings and sculptures, on display at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.
